16 (C) Is capable of continuously recording cardiac dysrhythmia at the scene with a
17 mechanism for transfer and storage or for printing for review subsequent to use.
18 (2) 'Emergency action plan' means the plan established pursuant to paragraph (5) of
19 subsection (c) of this Code section to provide for an emergency response to a person in
20 cardiac arrest.
21 (3) 'Internal response team' means the team of school personnel established pursuant to
22 paragraph (7) of subsection (c) of this Code section responsible for oversight of an
23 emergency response to a person in cardiac arrest and implementation of the emergency
24 action plan.
25 (4) 'School' means a public school in this state which provides K-12 education.
26 (b) No later than July 1, 2025, each school in this state shall have at least one functional
27 automated external defibrillator on site at such school at all times and easily accessible
28 during all school hours and during any school related function, including athletic practices,
29 athletic competitions, and other occasions where students and others will be present, for
30 use during emergencies.
31 (c) Each school shall:
32 (1) Ensure that each member of the internal response team and any other expected users
33 of the automated external defibrillator receive American Heart Association or American
34 Red Cross training in cardiopulmonary resuscitation and automated external defibrillator
35 use or complete an equivalent nationally recognized course;
36 (2) Notify the appropriate emergency medical services system of the existence and
37 location of each automated external defibrillator prior to said automated external
38 defibrillator being placed in use;
39 (3) Ensure that the automated external defibrillator is maintained and tested according
40 to the manufacturer's operational guidelines;
41 (4) Ensure that there is involvement of a licensed physician or other person authorized
42 by the Georgia Composite Medical Board in the site's automated external defibrillator
