43 program to ensure compliance with requirements for training, notification, and
44 maintenance;
45 (5)(4) Establish a written emergency action plan that adheres to nationally recognized
46 standards and that establishes specific steps to take during a cardiac emergency in a
47 school setting. Such plan shall be designed to provide for an effective system for
48 communication between members of the internal response team and other school
49 officials, ensuring that the internal response team or other designated personnel activate
50 the emergency medical services system as soon as reasonably possible after any person
51 renders emergency care or treatment to a person in cardiac arrest by using an automated
52 external defibrillator and report any clinical use of the automated external defibrillator
53 to the licensed physician or other person authorized by the Georgia Composite Medical
54 Board who is supervising the program, and ensuring that emergency medical services
55 personnel are led directly to the exact location of the person in cardiac arrest;
56 (6)(5) Beginning in the 2025-2026 school year and each school year thereafter, conduct
57 a minimum of two emergency action plan practice drills per school year, with at least one
58 per semester. One such practice drill may be a tabletop drill to walk through a
59 hypothetical scenario and the courses of action a school will need to take before, during,
60 and after a cardiac emergency. The emergency action plan practice drills shall include
61 various locations on school grounds and responses to different hypothetical situations;
62 (7)(6) Establish a designated internal response team composed of:
63 (A) At least five school staff members;
64 (B) One or more designated team leads trained in cardiopulmonary resuscitation and
65 automated external defibrillator use and responsible for oversight of an emergency
66 response;
67 (C) One or more designated cardiopulmonary resuscitation leads trained in
68 cardiopulmonary resuscitation and automated external defibrillator use;
