72 (E) One or more designated communication leads responsible for activating the
73 emergency medical services system, facilitating directions to the person in cardiac
74 arrest for emergency medical services personnel upon arrival at the school, and
75 coordinating communications with the designated team lead or leads; and
76 (8)(7) Apprise all school personnel of the location of automated external defibrillators
77 and the members of the internal response team.
78 (d) Subject to appropriations by the General Assembly, the Department of Education shall
79 provide funds to local school systems to assist in the purchase of automated external
80 defibrillators pursuant to this Code section.
81 (e) The department and local school systems shall use diligent efforts to identify private
82 sources of funding or donation of funding and equipment to meet the requirements of this
83 Code section."
84 SECTION 2.
85 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
